CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 9, 1967, pg. 15, reads: On Bus Tour - The Socialites Club, composed of Daughter Elks, are pictured just before boarding two Greyhound buses to go on a 16-day tour. After attending the Elks convention in Los Angeles, the group planned to visit 14 states before returning to Pittsburgh.  in picture are Chairman Alice Rose and Co-chairmen Madie Jordan, Catherine Johnson, Hester Thomas and Dorothy Lowery.  Hattie McClain is president.  Other dignitaries on the trip are Florence Taylor, Lottie Tibbs, Evelyn Nelson and Lucille Elliott. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of The Socialites Club members, including Alice Rose, Madie Jordan, Catherine Johnson, Hester Thomas, Dorothy Lowery, Hattie McClain, Florence Taylor, Lottie Tibbs, Evelyn Nelson, and Lucille Elliott, pose in front of Greyhound bus for trip to Elks Convention in Los Angeles, another version
